The US changes the rules for receipt of a visa
The persons must introduce themselves before their discussion at the consulate at the service offices for visa applications; the costs will be reduced in such a way.
As of 10 January 2011, the procedures for application of a visa are changed in the United States and the Consulates' message.
In the new procedure, most applicants must present themselves in the consulate before their discussion at the service offices for visa applications (ASC, initial letters in English).
The staff of the ASC shall record the biometric data of the applicant, which will be reviewed by the consulate prior to the discussion.
The new procedure has certain benefits for aspirants, including:
The total costs for the processing of the visa are reduced, as it is no longer necessary to pay separately the appointment, the processing of the visa application and the transport service to which the document is handled.
The applicant shall provide only one payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the counterpart to 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for visa with application (including visa for time workers) and 390 dollars for hands and investors.
Those who only wish to extend their visa do not have to have a conversation in the consulate, they must imagine only at the nearest ASC where they submit their documents and take their fingerprints.
As biometric data are collected in the ASC, the applicants who need a second date for the consulate will remain there less time than before.
Those who request the visa in the consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo do not have to pay the service surcharge of 26 dollars anymore.
Additional information on the new visa application procedure can be found on the following website: http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
